generateAttributedLabel

public java.text.AttributedString generateAttributedLabel(XYDataset dataset,
                                                          int series)
Generates an attributed label for the specified series, or null if no attributed label is available (in which case, the string returned by generateLabel(XYDataset, int) will provide the fallback). Only certain attributes are recognised by the code that ultimately displays the labels:
  • TextAttribute.FONT: will set the font;
  • TextAttribute.POSTURE: a value of TextAttribute.POSTURE_OBLIQUE will add Font.ITALIC to the current font;
  • TextAttribute.WEIGHT: a value of TextAttribute.WEIGHT_BOLD will add Font.BOLD to the current font;
  • TextAttribute.FOREGROUND: this will set the Paint for the current
  • TextAttribute.SUPERSCRIPT: the values TextAttribute.SUPERSCRIPT_SUB and TextAttribute.SUPERSCRIPT_SUPER are recognised.

Specified by:
generateAttributedLabel in interface XYSeriesLabelGenerator
Parameters:
dataset - the dataset.
series - the series index.
Returns:
An attributed label (possibly null).
